.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:75:- Stage P4b's runtime resolver build - [why] delivered in the sibling `011-runtime-engine`, not authored in this phase. (P4b has since consumed this phase's binding and flipped these activation manifests `legacy → compiled`; that flip is 011's work, held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag.)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:88:> All activation state is phase-local under `activation/`. Live runtime routing files remain read-only. P4a bound the candidate shadow-only with legacy serving; the sibling P4b flip (`011`) has since advanced these manifests to `servingAuthority: compiled`, `shadowOnly: false` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:97:### P0 - Blockers (MUST complete)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:101:| REQ-001 | Bind each of the seven hubs' compiled generation as `selectedPolicy` via a fenced CAS, advancing `fencingEpoch` `0 → 1`, while `servingAuthority` stays `legacy` and `shadowOnly` stays `true`. | Each hub's `manifest.json` binds `selectedPolicy` = the hub's compiled generation; P4a held `servingAuthority: "legacy"`, `shadowOnly: true` at fence epoch 1, and the sibling P4b flip (`011`) has since advanced the committed state to `servingAuthority: "compiled"`, `shadowOnly: false` (sk-code at fence epoch 4), retaining a byte-identical `manifest.serving-prior.json` for rollback. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:102:| REQ-002 | Gate every activation on the frozen benchmark scorer: re-hash the three shared scorer files and abort on any drift from the pinned digests. | The driver re-hashes `router-replay.cjs`, `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`, and `load-playbook-scenarios.cjs`; a digest mismatch aborts before any manifest write; records report `scorerFrozen=true`. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:103:| REQ-003 | Gate every activation on the child's canary: run the child's `harness/validate-canary.cjs` and abort on a non-zero exit. | A non-GREEN canary (route-gold not green, rollback not pass, serving-authority not legacy, or protected-digest drift) aborts activation; records report `canaryGreen=true`. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:108:### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:112:| REQ-007 | P4a T9 — real-model routing verification per hub on playbook prompts (GPT-5.6-LUNA high/fast, GPT-SOL medium/fast, MiniMax M3). | Complete: recorded in `real-model/<hub>/verdict.json` and each record's `realModelVerification` field; 40/42 pass across 3 models × 7 hubs, **0 wrong-hub routes** (the 2 non-passes are LUNA transport timeouts, correct on run2). Breadth is bounded (2 playbook prompts per hub) and honestly labeled — a sample, not full-corpus. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:113:| REQ-008 | Stage P4b — a runtime resolver that consumes `selectedPolicy`, plus a `servingAuthority` `legacy → compiled` flip, one hub at a time, with post-flip re-verification and proven rollback — delivered in the sibling `011-runtime-engine`. | Complete: the P4b runtime engine (`011`) is built and all 7 hubs are flipped `legacy → compiled` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag; each flip is canary-green via the real scorer, route-gold ROUTING byte-identical (only hashes changed), the 3 frozen scorer digests are unchanged, and the byte-exact rollback is retained (`manifest.serving-prior.json`). Commits: engine `d7da0fca43`, sk-code cutover `2fa3357f80`, remaining-6 cutover `337ca43cfa` (pushed on v4). |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:122:- **SC-001**: All seven hubs are bound — each `manifest.json` carries the compiled generation as `selectedPolicy`. P4a bound them at fence epoch 1 with `servingAuthority: "legacy"`, `shadowOnly: true`; the sibling P4b flip (`011`) has since moved the committed state to `servingAuthority: "compiled"`, `shadowOnly: false`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:124:- **SC-003**: The frozen-scorer pin and the canary green gate are enforced as hard preconditions; drift or a non-green canary aborts activation before any write.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:126:- **SC-005**: Stage P4b (runtime resolver + serving-authority flip) is complete in the sibling `011-runtime-engine` — all 7 hubs flipped `legacy → compiled`, held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag (routing byte-identical, so live routing is unchanged until the flag is enabled) and byte-exact-reversible — and T9 real-model verification is complete (0 wrong-hub routes). Post-flip real-model re-verification is treated as satisfied by the T9 result plus flag-off inertness; the advisor-hook machine-enforcement layer remains in progress — no premature "machine-enforced" claim.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:137:| Dependency | Per-hub shadow rollout children (prior/candidate manifests + `validate-canary.cjs`) | Cannot seed or gate activation without green canary children | Green: the driver seeds byte-for-byte from each child and runs the child's canary as a precondition |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:138:| Dependency | Frozen benchmark scorer (three pinned digests) | A drifted scorer would invalidate the canary baseline | The driver re-hashes all three files and aborts on any drift before writing |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:139:| Risk | Conflating "bind" with "serve" | The highest-blast change (live routing) becomes inseparable from governance binding | Two-stage split: P4a binds `selectedPolicy` only; P4b (serving flip) is a separate stage, executed in `011` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:141:| Risk | P4b blast radius | The serving-authority flip is the only stage that changes runtime routing | Executed one-hub-at-a-time behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag; reversible per-hub (retained serving-prior) or fleet-wide (flag off); route-gold ROUTING byte-identical, so live routing is unchanged until the flag is enabled |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:142:| Risk | Activation mutating a completed child | A write under a child path would break a proven canary | Structural rule: activation state is confined to `activation/`; the driver never writes under a child |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:157:- **NFR-R02**: Because P4a is pre-effect (no runtime consumer exists), rollback is clean; the post-effect caveat (a served flip cannot be silently undone) applies only to P4b.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:160:- **NFR-A01**: Binding a generation as `selectedPolicy` never confers serving authority; `servingAuthority` stayed `legacy` throughout P4a (the separate P4b flip in `011` later moved it to `compiled`).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:171:- Scorer digest drift: the driver aborts before any manifest write; no partial activation is possible.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:172:- Non-green canary: a non-zero `validate-canary.cjs` exit aborts activation for that hub.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:192:| Risk | 16/25 | Governance binding is pre-effect and reversible; the real blast (P4b serving flip) is split out and executed in `011` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:203:- What sample breadth (per-hub playbook subset vs full corpus) should the P4a T9 real-model verification cover, and how is the bound recorded so it is not read as a full-corpus claim?
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:204:- What explicit signal gates the P4b cutover per hub (which green thresholds on route-gold + real models), and who authorizes the first `servingAuthority` flip?
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:205:- Do the four non-hub single-skill routers get an equivalent activation pass on their `fenced-manifest.cjs` archetype, and if so under which follow-up packet?
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:3:description: "Three decisions governing whether and how SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING becomes the repo's effective default: defer global default-on to a staged P4 outcome, single-source compiled eligibility to a valid fresh manifest, and remediate the runtime-to-spec-tree resolver coupling."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:5:  - "compiled routing default-on decision record"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:12:    packet_pointer: "sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:16:    next_safe_action: "Begin P0 on operator go-ahead"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:28:      - "Flip the default now or adopt the phased path? Adopt the phased path (ADR-001), settled on the analysis; operator may override."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:35:<!-- HVR_REFERENCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/hvr-rules.md -->
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:40:## ADR-001: Defer global default-on to a staged P4 outcome
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:55:The parent goal asks to make compiled routing the effective default, framing it as flipping `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` from off to on. Reading the live integration point shows that framing buys nothing and costs real surface. The advisor enters compiled routing only through `enrichCompiledRoutes()` at `advisor-recommend.ts:357`. With the flag unset that function returns its input untouched (`:362`). With the flag set it maps over recommendations the legacy path already computed and attaches `compiledRoute` as an additive sibling field, `{ ...recommendation, compiledRoute }` at `:371`, and never recomputes the chosen `skillId` or `workflowMode`. Turning the flag on can only make that extra field appear or, on drift, silently not appear. It cannot change which skill is recommended.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:57:The sibling `011-runtime-engine` already flipped all seven hubs' manifests to `servingAuthority: compiled`, held inert behind the default-off flag. So the destination machinery exists. What does not exist is the reason to flip: today the flip is behavior-neutral by construction.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:62:- The three frozen benchmark scorer files (`router-replay.cjs`, `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`, `load-playbook-scenarios.cjs`) are pinned and never edited.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:63:- `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is absent from `ENV-REFERENCE.md`, which CLAUDE.md section 6 mandates as the source of truth for flag defaults. Flipping an undocumented flag violates that mandate.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:64:- The serve-time shim recomputes each hub's decision from live config and falls back to a `{ servingAuthority: "legacy" }` sentinel on any mismatch (`compiled-route.cjs:36-39`), which the advisor maps to `undefined` (`advisor-recommend.ts:351`). Editing a hub reverts it to legacy until re-minted, with nothing to observe the reversion.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:73:**We chose**: Treat global default-on as the final outcome of a four-step program (P0 through P4), not a one-line default change made now.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:75:**How it works**: P0 documents the flag in `ENV-REFERENCE.md` and makes the verify harness distinguish drift-to-legacy from breakage plus a per-hub serving-status readout. P1 adds a drift-detection CI that recomputes each hub's live hash against its minted manifest and fails re-mint-required. P2 canaries default-on in one env profile while the repo default stays off. P3 replaces the two hardcoded allowlists with a data-driven eligibility rule (see ADR-002). P4 flips the repo default hub-by-hub, keeping `=0` as the documented kill-switch. The flip becomes worthwhile precisely when compiled routing does something legacy cannot (a consumed decision, a caught drift), which P0 through P3 create.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:77:**Settlement**: This ruling is settled on the merits of the analysis above (the five premise-failures and the resolver coupling), as the session directive to settle the decision using the fresh-Opus analysis requires. It is a reversible documentation decision: no runtime change follows from it, and the operator may override to flip-now at any time. Acceptance settles the sequencing (phased) only; a separate operator go-ahead gates the start of P0 implementation.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:88:| **Phased P0 to P4 (chosen)** | Reversible at every step; drift caught by CI not production; flag documented before it is load-bearing; the flip lands when it carries benefit | Four phases of enabling work before the headline default flips | 9/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:89:| Flip the repo default now | One-line change; matches the literal goal wording | Zero routing benefit (additive metadata only); normalizes silent drift; inverts the kill-switch (absence becomes compiled); violates the ENV-REFERENCE governance mandate | 3/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:90:| Abandon compiled routing | Removes the drift surface entirely | Discards a built, proven, reversible system and the parity work behind it; loses the future benefit the phased path unlocks | 2/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:92:**Why this one**: The destination (compiled as the effective default) is not rejected, it is sequenced. Flipping today trades governance and observability surface for a benefit that is currently zero, so the correct move is to build the benefit and the safety net first, then flip. The steelman for flipping now is honest and recorded: if compiled cannot help and cannot hurt routing, the only net effects are the ones that can hurt, so flip it once compiled does something legacy cannot. That condition is exactly what P0 through P3 establish.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:102:- The eventual flip is observable: a per-hub readout shows compiled-serving vs legacy-fallback vs drifted, so a red signal means breakage rather than routine churn.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:104:- The kill-switch stays meaningful: `=0` remains the documented control, and variable-absence keeps its safe legacy meaning until the P4 flip deliberately changes it.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:107:- Four phases of enabling work precede the headline default change. Mitigation: each phase ships standalone value (docs, CI, canary, single-sourced eligibility) rather than being pure overhead.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:113:| Operator overrides to flip now | M | The fallback is genuinely fail-safe today, so an early flip is survivable; but P0 documentation and observability should still land first to satisfy governance and avoid a two-meaning red signal |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:125:| 1 | **Necessary?** | PASS | The governance gap (undocumented flag) and the silent-drift surface are real today, independent of any future flip |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:129:| 5 | **Open Horizons?** | PASS | Data-driven eligibility (ADR-002) scales to every future skill, so the path does not paint the fleet into a hardcoded corner |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:141:- P0: `ENV-REFERENCE.md` gains the flag entry; the verify harness gains drift-vs-breakage classification and a per-hub serving-status readout.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:142:- P1: a drift-detection CI job plus the enforced rule that editing a hub's routing inputs re-mints its manifest in the same change.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:143:- P2 to P4: a canary env profile, the data-driven eligibility rule (ADR-002), then the staged hub-by-hub default flip.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:145:**How to roll back**: Nothing in this phase changes runtime behavior, so there is nothing to roll back here. Across the program, `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` restores legacy serving fleet-wide, and each per-hub flip retains a byte-identical prior manifest for a byte-exact per-hub revert.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:159:| **Status** | Accepted (design direction; implemented in P3) |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:168:Which hubs are compiled-eligible is hardcoded in two places: `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` in `advisor-recommend.ts:41` and `HUB_CHILD` in `compiled-route.cjs:23`. Two hand-maintained lists drift apart. A newly created skill is compiled-invisible with no defined way to opt in, and `create-skill` today has zero compiled-routing awareness (a repo grep for compiled-routing tokens under the create-skill mode returns nothing).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:172:- Backward-compat is required: a skill lacking the compiled JSONs or snapshot must route via legacy with no behavior change.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:182:**We chose**: Define compiled eligibility as a single derived predicate: a hub is compiled-eligible if and only if a valid, fresh manifest exists for it (its minted digest matches its live config hash). Both `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` and `HUB_CHILD` derive from that one rule.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:184:**How it works**: Onboarding a skill means minting its manifest; backward-compat means the absence of a manifest yields legacy by construction. `create-skill` (phase 013) mints or scaffolds the manifest step so new hubs are born either compiled-ready or explicitly legacy, never silently half-wired.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:196:| One hardcoded list imported by both | Removes duplication cheaply | Still manual; a new skill still needs a code edit to onboard | 6/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:210:- A new or edited skill has one clear compiled state derived from whether its manifest is fresh.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:220:| Migration removes the hardcoded sets prematurely | M | Keep the sets as a pinned fallback until P3 parity is proven, then delete in one change |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:231:| 1 | **Necessary?** | PASS | Two hardcoded allowlists exist now and will diverge; new skills have no onboarding path |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:234:| 4 | **Fits Goal?** | PASS | Directly enables a safe global default-on by making eligibility a maintained property, not a code constant |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:235:| 5 | **Open Horizons?** | PASS | Scales to any number of future skills with no code edit per skill |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:247:- P3: a single eligibility predicate keyed on manifest freshness; `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` and `HUB_CHILD` become derived, then removed as hand-authored constants.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:248:- Phase 013: `create-skill` scaffolds the manifest step so onboarding mints eligibility.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:250:**How to roll back**: Retain the hardcoded sets as a pinned fallback through P3; if the derived predicate misbehaves, restore the constants (a one-file revert in each of the two locations).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:264:| **Status** | Accepted (P0 remediation; promote the resolver) |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:273:The runtime front door `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` resolves its resolver from a path inside the spec tree: `compiled-route.cjs:16-21` points at `007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs`. This repo renumbers and re-nests spec folders constantly (the memory index records repeated hyphen migrations, renumbers, and re-nests). A single such move silently breaks every compiled route to the legacy sentinel, with no observable signal. The repo's own reorganization is a latent drift engine independent of hub-config edits.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:300:| **Promote resolver to a runtime path (chosen)** | Removes the drift source rather than guarding it; runtime no longer depends on spec-tree layout | A small build or copy step to keep the runtime copy current | 8/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:302:| Leave as-is and document | No work now | The drift source remains and stays silent; documentation does not stop a renumber | 4/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:324:| Runtime copy goes stale vs authored source | M | Add a freshness check to the drift-CI (P1) so a stale runtime resolver fails the same gate as a stale manifest |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:338:| 4 | **Fits Goal?** | PASS | A default-on fleet cannot rest on a resolver that a spec move can sever |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:351:- P0: move `resolve.cjs` to a runtime path; update the shim's require; keep the authored source building or copying into place.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:352:- P1: the drift-CI also checks the runtime resolver is current with its authored source.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:364:HVR rules: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/hvr-rules.md
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:3:description: "How the fenced-CAS activation driver binds each hub's compiled generation, proves byte-exact rollback, and stages the now-complete runtime cutover (P4b executed in 011-runtime-engine)."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:7:  - "P4a P4b staging"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:34:| **Serving authority (P4a)** | Legacy remains authoritative; the compiled generation is *bound*, not *served* |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:39:A single shared driver, `lib/activate-hub.cjs`, performs the design-faithful activation for every hub: it seeds a phase-local activation manifest byte-for-byte from the hub's shadow rollout child, then binds the hub's compiled generation as `selectedPolicy` via a fenced CAS that advances the fence epoch while `servingAuthority` stays `legacy`. Every activation is gated on a frozen-scorer pin and a green canary, and proves a byte-exact rollback. Stage P4b — the runtime resolver plus the `servingAuthority` flip — is complete, delivered in the sibling `011-runtime-engine`: all seven hubs were flipped `legacy → compiled` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag, with the byte-identical legacy manifest retained per hub.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:49:- [x] Each hub's shadow rollout child is present with prior/candidate manifests and a green `validate-canary.cjs`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:54:- [x] All seven hubs bind their compiled generation as `selectedPolicy`, fence epoch `0 → 1`, `servingAuthority: legacy`, `shadowOnly: true`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:56:- [x] Frozen-scorer pin and canary green gate enforced as hard preconditions.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:58:- [x] P4a T9 real-model routing verification recorded per hub (complete; 40/42 pass, **0 wrong-hub routes** across 3 models × 7 hubs).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:59:- [x] P4b runtime resolver + serving-authority flip complete in `011-runtime-engine` (all 7 hubs flipped `legacy → compiled`, inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag, byte-exact rollback retained).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:70:Bind-then-serve, split into two stages. Activation is a fenced compare-and-swap that moves `selectedPolicy` from the legacy generation to the compiled generation on a phase-local manifest; it never edits a serving policy. Serving authority stayed legacy through P4a; the separate P4b resolver (`011-runtime-engine`) has since been built and flipped all seven hubs to `compiled` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:74:- **`activation/<hub>/manifest.json`**: the serving manifest carrying `selectedPolicy`, `servingAuthority`, and `fencingEpoch`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:80:Shadow rollout child (`manifest.prior.json` / `manifest.candidate.json`) → byte-for-byte seed into `activation/<hub>/` → frozen-scorer pin + canary green gate → fenced CAS binds `candidatePolicy` as `selectedPolicy`, advances the fence epoch (`servingAuthority` stays `legacy`) → temp-dir rollback proof restores the byte-identical prior manifest → `activation-record.json` emitted.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:94:| `harness/validate-canary.cjs` (per child) | Canary green gate | Executed as an activation precondition | Non-zero exit aborts; records report `canaryGreen=true` |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:95:| Three shared scorer files | Frozen route-gold scorer | Re-hashed, never edited | Pinned digests unchanged; drift aborts before any write |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:96:| `activation/<hub>/manifest.json` | New per-hub serving manifest | Fenced CAS writes `selectedPolicy`, advances fence; P4b (`011`) later flips serving authority | P4a: `servingAuthority: legacy`, `shadowOnly: true`, fence epoch 1 → post-P4b (current committed): `servingAuthority: compiled`, `shadowOnly: false` |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:112:- [x] Author the shared `lib/activate-hub.cjs` driver (frozen-scorer pin, canary green gate, byte-for-byte seed).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:113:- [x] Frozen-scorer gate: re-hash `router-replay.cjs`, `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`, `load-playbook-scenarios.cjs`; abort on any drift.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:114:- [x] Canary gate: execute each child's `harness/validate-canary.cjs`; abort on non-zero exit.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:119:- [x] Keep `servingAuthority: legacy` and `shadowOnly: true` across the swap — bind, do not serve.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:136:| Precondition | Frozen-scorer pin; canary green gate | Driver re-hash + child `validate-canary.cjs` |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:151:| Shadow rollout children (per hub) | Internal | Green | No seed source or canary gate without green children |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:152:| Frozen benchmark scorer (three pinned digests) | Internal | Green | Drift would invalidate the canary baseline; driver aborts |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:154:| Real models (LUNA / SOL / MiniMax) | External | Complete | T9 verification done (0 wrong-hub routes); did not block the P4a binding |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:163:- **Trigger**: Any activation-time abort (scorer drift, non-green canary, seed-hash mismatch, or fence-epoch mismatch), or a decision to unbind a hub during the bake window.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:164:- **Procedure**: Restore the retained prior manifest via the fenced CAS and confirm `restoredHash` equals the accepted `priorManifestHash`; because P4a is pre-effect (legacy still serves), no runtime routing change needs undoing. Retain the prior manifest for the full bake window before any cleanup.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:181:| Verify | Core | Real-model verification (T9), P4b gate |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:212:3. Confirm `selectedPolicy` reverts to the prior generation and `servingAuthority` remains `legacy`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:215:- **Has runtime effect?** No — P4a is pre-effect; legacy keeps serving.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:216:- **Reversal procedure**: Byte-exact manifest restore; no external COMMITted effect exists to undo (the post-effect caveat applies to P4b only).
