.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:38:<!-- HVR_REFERENCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/hvr-rules.md -->
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:43:## Metadata
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:47:| **Status** | Ruling settled (adopt the phased path P0->P4, decided on the analysis; reversible and operator-overridable). No runtime implementation started; a separate operator go-ahead gates P0. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:51:| **Repository default** | Unchanged; compiled routing remains default-off |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:58:## Executive Summary
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:60:The decision packet settles the ruling on the analysis: adopt a staged path to compiled routing as the effective default rather than flipping the default now. No runtime work has begun. The current live integration remains additive metadata only, the compiled and legacy decisions remain identical, and the repository flag remains off by default. The operator may override the ruling to flip-now at any time; that override is available but not blocking.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:62:The planned program starts by documenting and observing the existing behavior, then adds drift enforcement, a bounded canary, data-driven eligibility, and finally a reversible hub-by-hub default change. The three benchmark scorer files remain pinned throughout.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:68:## What Was Built
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:70:### P0: Governance, Observability, and Resolver Stability
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:72:Document the environment flag, distinguish drift-to-legacy from resolver breakage, expose serving status per hub, and remove or explicitly guard the runtime dependency on a spec-tree path.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:74:### P1 and P2: Enforcement and Canary
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:76:Add re-mint-required CI for stale manifests, then enable compiled routing in one named environment profile while the repository default remains off.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:78:### P3 and P4: Eligibility and Effective Default
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:80:Derive both eligibility consumers from the manifest-freshness rule already owned by `decision-record.md`, then stage the global default one hub at a time while preserving `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the fleet-wide kill-switch.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:88:## How It Was Delivered
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:90:Delivery follows the ordered gates in `plan.md`: an operator go-ahead to begin, P0 safety surface, P1 drift enforcement, P2 canary, P3 derived eligibility, and P4 staged cutover. Each stage records parity, status, rollback, and scorer-integrity evidence before the next stage can begin. The implementation stops at the first failed gate.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:96:## Architecture Decisions Summary
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:102:| Treat global default-on as the P4 outcome | Accepted | No default change before P0-P3 evidence |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:103:| Derive eligibility from a valid fresh manifest | Accepted (implemented in P3) | Future onboarding and both runtime consumers share one rule |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:104:| Promote the resolver to a stable runtime path | Accepted (implemented in P0) | Spec-tree renames stop being a silent runtime drift source |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:110:## Key Decisions
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:114:| Keep the repository default off during documentation, drift CI, and the canary | The current compiled path changes no routing decisions, so safety and observability must land before the default carries operational weight. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:116:| Keep rollback stage-local | A failed canary or eligibility change should not discard earlier governance and diagnostic improvements. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:117:| Make sibling packets consume these contracts | One authoritative fallback and eligibility definition prevents create-skill and benchmark behavior from diverging. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:123:## Verification
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:130:| Drift CI and status readout | Planned for P0-P1 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:131:| Canary and kill-switch drill | Planned for P2 and P4 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:133:| Spec-folder strict validation | Run: `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh .opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision --strict`; Errors zero |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:139:## Milestone Status
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:144:| M1 P0 safety surface | Planned | No implementation evidence |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:145:| M2 P1 drift enforcement | Planned | No implementation evidence |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:146:| M3 P2 canary | Planned | Canary profile not selected |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:147:| M4 P3 eligibility | Planned | Current allowlists remain hand-maintained |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:148:| M5 P4 effective default | Planned | Repository default remains off |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:154:## Known Limitations
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:157:2. **The flag is still undocumented in the environment reference.** That gap is P0 implementation work, not work performed by this authoring phase.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:158:3. **Drift and breakage are not yet distinguishable in the live verification surface.** The planned P0 harness change owns that distinction.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:159:4. **Eligibility is still duplicated.** The P3 implementation has not replaced the current hand-maintained sets.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:160:5. **The resolver still depends on the current runtime path arrangement.** P0 must promote it or record and guard an approved exception.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:166:## Follow-ups
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:169:- [ ] Choose the P2 canary environment profile and promotion owner.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:170:- [ ] Resolve the P0 architecture choice: promote the resolver to a stable runtime location or approve a guarded residual coupling.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:171:- [ ] Implement P0-P4 runtime, CI, environment, and hub-directive changes outside this documentation-only authoring pass.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:172:- [ ] Implement create-skill onboarding alignment in the dependent packet after the P3 minter and eligibility interfaces are stable.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:173:- [ ] Implement Lane C compiled-path parity and drift fixtures in the dependent benchmark packet without editing the frozen scorer files.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/implementation-summary.md:179:## Deviations from Plan
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:3:description: "Activate the compiled router contract across all seven parent hubs in two ordered stages. Stage P4a (design-faithful): a fenced compare-and-swap binds each hub's compiled policy generation as the SELECTED policy on a dedicated per-hub activation manifest, advancing a monotonic fence epoch, while serving authority stays legacy and no runtime consumer is touched; rollback restores the byte-identical prior manifest. Stage P4b (literal cutover, now complete in the sibling 011-runtime-engine): a runtime resolver consumes the compiled contract and serving authority was flipped hub-by-hub across all seven hubs, re-verified, with the byte-identical legacy manifest retained for rollback and the compiled path held inert behind the default-off SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING flag. The shared benchmark scorer is frozen and pinned throughout; every activation proves a byte-exact rollback and rides a green canary."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:18:- Scope drift, vague acceptance criteria, and optimistic done-language without evidence.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:21:# Unified Router Refactor — Live Activation
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:23:## EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:27:Every parent hub already owns a real-green rollout canary: its authored routing (`SKILL.md` + `hub-router.json` + `mode-registry.json`) is projected into a content-addressed `CompiledPolicyV1`, proven route-gold byte-green against the real read-only benchmark scorer, closed-algebra-valid, and reversible by a byte-exact shadow rollback. What did **not** exist was an activation layer: a place where the compiled generation is *bound* as authoritative, distinct from where it is *served*. Stage P4a builds exactly that layer, and it is this phase's shipped work; Stage P4b — the only stage that changes what actually routes — is now complete: executed in the sibling `011-runtime-engine`, which flipped all seven hubs' serving authority `legacy → compiled` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag (route-gold ROUTING byte-identical — only hashes changed), with a byte-identical legacy manifest retained per hub for a byte-exact rollback.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:32:## 1. METADATA
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:37:| **Priority** | P0 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:38:| **Status** | Complete — P4a design-faithful activation + T9 real-model verification (0 wrong-hub routes) complete for all 7 hubs, and the P4b literal cutover (`011-runtime-engine`) is complete: all 7 hubs flipped `legacy → compiled` (`servingAuthority: compiled`, `shadowOnly: false`), inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag, byte-exact rollback retained. Advisor-hook machine-enforcement remains in progress |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:41:| **Migration stage** | Stage P4a — design-faithful activation (bind, do not serve); the sibling P4b flip (`011`) has since advanced serving authority to compiled |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:42:| **Blast radius** | Governance binding (selectedPolicy CAS) — reversible, pre-effect; the P4b runtime flip (`011`) is complete but held inert by default behind `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` and reversible per-hub or fleet-wide |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:48:## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:50:### Problem Statement
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:54:### Purpose
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:56:Establish a phase-local activation layer that binds each hub's compiled generation as `selectedPolicy` through a fenced compare-and-swap while leaving `servingAuthority` at `legacy`, proves a byte-exact rollback for every activation, and provides the proven, reversible foundation that the subsequent P4b flip (executed in `011-runtime-engine`) built on to move all seven hubs to compiled serving behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:63:## 3. SCOPE
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:65:### In Scope
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:70:- The frozen-scorer pin, the canary green gate, and the byte-exact rollback proof that every activation must clear.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:72:### Out of Scope
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:74:- The four non-hub single-skill routers - [why] different archetype (`fenced-manifest.cjs`, no `acceptance.json`), not in the seven-hub activation order.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:75:- Stage P4b's runtime resolver build - [why] delivered in the sibling `011-runtime-engine`, not authored in this phase. (P4b has since consumed this phase's binding and flipped these activation manifests `legacy → compiled`; that flip is 011's work, held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag.)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:76:- Any edit to a live `SKILL.md`, `hub-router.json`, `mode-registry.json`, or the frozen benchmark scorer - [why] activation binds a generation; it never edits a serving policy or a protected input.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:78:### Files to Change
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:88:> All activation state is phase-local under `activation/`. Live runtime routing files remain read-only. P4a bound the candidate shadow-only with legacy serving; the sibling P4b flip (`011`) has since advanced these manifests to `servingAuthority: compiled`, `shadowOnly: false` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:95:## 4. REQUIREMENTS
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:97:### P0 - Blockers (MUST complete)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:101:| REQ-001 | Bind each of the seven hubs' compiled generation as `selectedPolicy` via a fenced CAS, advancing `fencingEpoch` `0 → 1`, while `servingAuthority` stays `legacy` and `shadowOnly` stays `true`. | Each hub's `manifest.json` binds `selectedPolicy` = the hub's compiled generation; P4a held `servingAuthority: "legacy"`, `shadowOnly: true` at fence epoch 1, and the sibling P4b flip (`011`) has since advanced the committed state to `servingAuthority: "compiled"`, `shadowOnly: false` (sk-code at fence epoch 4), retaining a byte-identical `manifest.serving-prior.json` for rollback. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:102:| REQ-002 | Gate every activation on the frozen benchmark scorer: re-hash the three shared scorer files and abort on any drift from the pinned digests. | The driver re-hashes `router-replay.cjs`, `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`, and `load-playbook-scenarios.cjs`; a digest mismatch aborts before any manifest write; records report `scorerFrozen=true`. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:103:| REQ-003 | Gate every activation on the child's canary: run the child's `harness/validate-canary.cjs` and abort on a non-zero exit. | A non-GREEN canary (route-gold not green, rollback not pass, serving-authority not legacy, or protected-digest drift) aborts activation; records report `canaryGreen=true`. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:108:### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:112:| REQ-007 | P4a T9 — real-model routing verification per hub on playbook prompts (GPT-5.6-LUNA high/fast, GPT-SOL medium/fast, MiniMax M3). | Complete: recorded in `real-model/<hub>/verdict.json` and each record's `realModelVerification` field; 40/42 pass across 3 models × 7 hubs, **0 wrong-hub routes** (the 2 non-passes are LUNA transport timeouts, correct on run2). Breadth is bounded (2 playbook prompts per hub) and honestly labeled — a sample, not full-corpus. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:113:| REQ-008 | Stage P4b — a runtime resolver that consumes `selectedPolicy`, plus a `servingAuthority` `legacy → compiled` flip, one hub at a time, with post-flip re-verification and proven rollback — delivered in the sibling `011-runtime-engine`. | Complete: the P4b runtime engine (`011`) is built and all 7 hubs are flipped `legacy → compiled` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag; each flip is canary-green via the real scorer, route-gold ROUTING byte-identical (only hashes changed), the 3 frozen scorer digests are unchanged, and the byte-exact rollback is retained (`manifest.serving-prior.json`). Commits: engine `d7da0fca43`, sk-code cutover `2fa3357f80`, remaining-6 cutover `337ca43cfa` (pushed on v4). |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:120:## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:122:- **SC-001**: All seven hubs are bound — each `manifest.json` carries the compiled generation as `selectedPolicy`. P4a bound them at fence epoch 1 with `servingAuthority: "legacy"`, `shadowOnly: true`; the sibling P4b flip (`011`) has since moved the committed state to `servingAuthority: "compiled"`, `shadowOnly: false`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:124:- **SC-003**: The frozen-scorer pin and the canary green gate are enforced as hard preconditions; drift or a non-green canary aborts activation before any write.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:126:- **SC-005**: Stage P4b (runtime resolver + serving-authority flip) is complete in the sibling `011-runtime-engine` — all 7 hubs flipped `legacy → compiled`, held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag (routing byte-identical, so live routing is unchanged until the flag is enabled) and byte-exact-reversible — and T9 real-model verification is complete (0 wrong-hub routes). Post-flip real-model re-verification is treated as satisfied by the T9 result plus flag-off inertness; the advisor-hook machine-enforcement layer remains in progress — no premature "machine-enforced" claim.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:133:## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:137:| Dependency | Per-hub shadow rollout children (prior/candidate manifests + `validate-canary.cjs`) | Cannot seed or gate activation without green canary children | Green: the driver seeds byte-for-byte from each child and runs the child's canary as a precondition |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:138:| Dependency | Frozen benchmark scorer (three pinned digests) | A drifted scorer would invalidate the canary baseline | The driver re-hashes all three files and aborts on any drift before writing |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:139:| Risk | Conflating "bind" with "serve" | The highest-blast change (live routing) becomes inseparable from governance binding | Two-stage split: P4a binds `selectedPolicy` only; P4b (serving flip) is a separate stage, executed in `011` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:141:| Risk | P4b blast radius | The serving-authority flip is the only stage that changes runtime routing | Executed one-hub-at-a-time behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag; reversible per-hub (retained serving-prior) or fleet-wide (flag off); route-gold ROUTING byte-identical, so live routing is unchanged until the flag is enabled |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:142:| Risk | Activation mutating a completed child | A write under a child path would break a proven canary | Structural rule: activation state is confined to `activation/`; the driver never writes under a child |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:149:## L2: NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:151:### Determinism
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:155:### Reversibility
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:157:- **NFR-R02**: Because P4a is pre-effect (no runtime consumer exists), rollback is clean; the post-effect caveat (a served flip cannot be silently undone) applies only to P4b.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:159:### Authority
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:160:- **NFR-A01**: Binding a generation as `selectedPolicy` never confers serving authority; `servingAuthority` stayed `legacy` throughout P4a (the separate P4b flip in `011` later moved it to `compiled`).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:168:## L2: EDGE CASES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:170:### Precondition failures
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:171:- Scorer digest drift: the driver aborts before any manifest write; no partial activation is possible.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:172:- Non-green canary: a non-zero `validate-canary.cjs` exit aborts activation for that hub.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:174:### Idempotency and re-runs
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:178:### Boundary integrity
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:187:## L2: COMPLEXITY ASSESSMENT
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:192:| Risk | 16/25 | Governance binding is pre-effect and reversible; the real blast (P4b serving flip) is split out and executed in `011` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:201:## 7. OPEN QUESTIONS
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:203:- What sample breadth (per-hub playbook subset vs full corpus) should the P4a T9 real-model verification cover, and how is the bound recorded so it is not read as a full-corpus claim?
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:204:- What explicit signal gates the P4b cutover per hub (which green thresholds on route-gold + real models), and who authorizes the first `servingAuthority` flip?
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/spec.md:205:- Do the four non-hub single-skill routers get an equivalent activation pass on their `fenced-manifest.cjs` archetype, and if so under which follow-up packet?
