.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/tasks.md:85:- [x] T016 P4b — build a runtime resolver that consumes `selectedPolicy` behind a flag (delivered in `011-runtime-engine`; inert by default, legacy reachable).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/tasks.md:86:- [x] T017 P4b — flip `servingAuthority` `legacy → compiled` one hub at a time with post-flip re-verification and proven rollback (all 7 hubs flipped via `011`; canary-green, route-gold byte-identical, byte-exact rollback retained).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/tasks.md:89:**Evidence**: P4a design-faithful activation, T9 real-model verification (0 wrong-hub routes), and the P4b cutover (T016-T017) are all complete for the 7 hubs — the seven-hub `legacy → compiled` flip landed in `011-runtime-engine` (commits engine `d7da0fca43`, sk-code cutover `2fa3357f80`, remaining-6 cutover `337ca43cfa`, pushed on v4), held inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag. The advisor-hook machine-enforcement layer remains in progress and is NOT claimed done.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/tasks.md:96:## Cross-References
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:3:description: "How the fenced-CAS activation driver binds each hub's compiled generation, proves byte-exact rollback, and stages the now-complete runtime cutover (P4b executed in 011-runtime-engine)."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:7:  - "P4a P4b staging"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:11:# Implementation Plan: Unified Router Refactor — Live Activation
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:26:## 1. SUMMARY
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:28:### Technical Context
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:34:| **Serving authority (P4a)** | Legacy remains authoritative; the compiled generation is *bound*, not *served* |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:37:### Overview
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:39:A single shared driver, `lib/activate-hub.cjs`, performs the design-faithful activation for every hub: it seeds a phase-local activation manifest byte-for-byte from the hub's shadow rollout child, then binds the hub's compiled generation as `selectedPolicy` via a fenced CAS that advances the fence epoch while `servingAuthority` stays `legacy`. Every activation is gated on a frozen-scorer pin and a green canary, and proves a byte-exact rollback. Stage P4b — the runtime resolver plus the `servingAuthority` flip — is complete, delivered in the sibling `011-runtime-engine`: all seven hubs were flipped `legacy → compiled` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag, with the byte-identical legacy manifest retained per hub.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:46:## 2. QUALITY GATES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:48:### Definition of Ready
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:49:- [x] Each hub's shadow rollout child is present with prior/candidate manifests and a green `validate-canary.cjs`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:53:### Definition of Done
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:54:- [x] All seven hubs bind their compiled generation as `selectedPolicy`, fence epoch `0 → 1`, `servingAuthority: legacy`, `shadowOnly: true`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:56:- [x] Frozen-scorer pin and canary green gate enforced as hard preconditions.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:58:- [x] P4a T9 real-model routing verification recorded per hub (complete; 40/42 pass, **0 wrong-hub routes** across 3 models × 7 hubs).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:59:- [x] P4b runtime resolver + serving-authority flip complete in `011-runtime-engine` (all 7 hubs flipped `legacy → compiled`, inert behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag, byte-exact rollback retained).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:66:## 3. ARCHITECTURE
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:68:### Pattern
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:70:Bind-then-serve, split into two stages. Activation is a fenced compare-and-swap that moves `selectedPolicy` from the legacy generation to the compiled generation on a phase-local manifest; it never edits a serving policy. Serving authority stayed legacy through P4a; the separate P4b resolver (`011-runtime-engine`) has since been built and flipped all seven hubs to `compiled` behind the default-off `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` flag.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:72:### Key Components
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:74:- **`activation/<hub>/manifest.json`**: the serving manifest carrying `selectedPolicy`, `servingAuthority`, and `fencingEpoch`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:78:### Data Flow
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:80:Shadow rollout child (`manifest.prior.json` / `manifest.candidate.json`) → byte-for-byte seed into `activation/<hub>/` → frozen-scorer pin + canary green gate → fenced CAS binds `candidatePolicy` as `selectedPolicy`, advances the fence epoch (`servingAuthority` stays `legacy`) → temp-dir rollback proof restores the byte-identical prior manifest → `activation-record.json` emitted.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:87:## FIX ADDENDUM: AFFECTED SURFACES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:94:| `harness/validate-canary.cjs` (per child) | Canary green gate | Executed as an activation precondition | Non-zero exit aborts; records report `canaryGreen=true` |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:95:| Three shared scorer files | Frozen route-gold scorer | Re-hashed, never edited | Pinned digests unchanged; drift aborts before any write |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:96:| `activation/<hub>/manifest.json` | New per-hub serving manifest | Fenced CAS writes `selectedPolicy`, advances fence; P4b (`011`) later flips serving authority | P4a: `servingAuthority: legacy`, `shadowOnly: true`, fence epoch 1 → post-P4b (current committed): `servingAuthority: compiled`, `shadowOnly: false` |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:97:| Live `SKILL.md` / `hub-router.json` / `mode-registry.json` | Authoritative serving routing | **Unchanged — not a consumer** | Activation confined to `010-live-activation/activation/` |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:109:## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:111:### Phase 1: Setup
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:112:- [x] Author the shared `lib/activate-hub.cjs` driver (frozen-scorer pin, canary green gate, byte-for-byte seed).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:113:- [x] Frozen-scorer gate: re-hash `router-replay.cjs`, `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`, `load-playbook-scenarios.cjs`; abort on any drift.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:114:- [x] Canary gate: execute each child's `harness/validate-canary.cjs`; abort on non-zero exit.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:117:### Phase 2: Core Implementation
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:119:- [x] Keep `servingAuthority: legacy` and `shadowOnly: true` across the swap — bind, do not serve.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:122:### Phase 3: Verification
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:132:## 5. TESTING STRATEGY
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:136:| Precondition | Frozen-scorer pin; canary green gate | Driver re-hash + child `validate-canary.cjs` |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:147:## 6. DEPENDENCIES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:151:| Shadow rollout children (per hub) | Internal | Green | No seed source or canary gate without green children |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:152:| Frozen benchmark scorer (three pinned digests) | Internal | Green | Drift would invalidate the canary baseline; driver aborts |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:154:| Real models (LUNA / SOL / MiniMax) | External | Complete | T9 verification done (0 wrong-hub routes); did not block the P4a binding |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:161:## 7. ROLLBACK PLAN
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:163:- **Trigger**: Any activation-time abort (scorer drift, non-green canary, seed-hash mismatch, or fence-epoch mismatch), or a decision to unbind a hub during the bake window.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:164:- **Procedure**: Restore the retained prior manifest via the fenced CAS and confirm `restoredHash` equals the accepted `priorManifestHash`; because P4a is pre-effect (legacy still serves), no runtime routing change needs undoing. Retain the prior manifest for the full bake window before any cleanup.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:171:## L2: PHASE DEPENDENCIES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:181:| Verify | Core | Real-model verification (T9), P4b gate |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:188:## L2: EFFORT ESTIMATION
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:202:## L2: ENHANCED ROLLBACK
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:204:### Pre-activation checklist
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:209:### Rollback procedure
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:212:3. Confirm `selectedPolicy` reverts to the prior generation and `servingAuthority` remains `legacy`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:214:### Data reversal
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:215:- **Has runtime effect?** No — P4a is pre-effect; legacy keeps serving.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/010-live-activation/plan.md:216:- **Reversal procedure**: Byte-exact manifest restore; no external COMMITted effect exists to undo (the post-effect caveat applies to P4b only).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:3:description: "Settle whether SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING should become the repo's effective default and, if so, on what safe path. The compiled router is built, wired, and inert behind a default-off flag: the P4b flip already moved all seven hubs' manifests to servingAuthority: compiled, and the live advisor consumes them only when the flag is 1, only for hubs in a hardcoded allowlist, and even then attaches the compiled decision as ADDITIVE metadata that never changes which skill is recommended. This phase records the decision — default-on is a Phase-4 OUTCOME, not a switch-flip — and specifies the four contracts that make an eventual global default-on safe and reversible: (P0) document the flag in ENV-REFERENCE and make the verify harness distinguish drift-to-legacy from breakage plus a per-hub serving-status readout; (P1) a drift-detection CI that recomputes each hub's live hash against its minted manifest and fails 're-mint required'; (P2) a canary default-on in one env profile with the repo default staying off; (P3) a data-driven eligibility rule (compiled-eligible IFF a valid fresh manifest exists) that single-sources the duplicated allowlist and makes no-manifest skills legacy by construction; (P4) a staged, hub-by-hub global default-on that flips the two code predicates and the seven SKILL.md directives in lockstep while keeping =0 as the documented kill-switch. The frozen benchmark scorer is never touched and every step is byte-exact reversible."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:5:  - "compiled routing default-on decision"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:6:  - "SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING flip default"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:12:    packet_pointer: "sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:16:    next_safe_action: "Begin P0 on operator go-ahead"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:28:      - "Flip the default now or adopt the phased path? Adopt the phased path, settled on the analysis; operator may override."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:37:- Scope drift, vague acceptance criteria, and optimistic done-language without evidence.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:40:# Compiled Routing — Default-On Decision & Safe-Cutover Contract
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:42:## EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:44:The compiled skill-router is built, hardened, wired into the live advisor, and **inert behind a default-off flag**. The sibling P4b work (`011-runtime-engine`) already flipped all seven hubs' activation manifests to `servingAuthority: compiled`; what remains gated is whether the runtime *consumes* that state, and that gate is `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING`. The parent goal asks to make compiled routing "the effective default."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:46:This phase is a **decision packet**, not a flip. It records — against verified source evidence, not narrative — that flipping the repo default to ON **today changes zero routing decisions** and therefore trades real operational surface for no behavioral gain, and it specifies the four contracts (P0→P4) under which a global default-on becomes a safe, observable, reversible *outcome*. The single load-bearing finding: in the only live integration point, the compiled decision is attached as **additive metadata** to a recommendation the legacy path has already computed — so enabling the flag can only make an extra `compiledRoute` field appear or silently not-appear; it cannot change which skill is recommended (`advisor-recommend.ts:357-374`, decisive line `:371`).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:48:The ruling is **settled: adopt the phased path** — decided on the analysis and source verification above (per the session directive to settle the decision), reversible, and open to operator override to flip-now. No runtime change follows from this decision; a separate operator go-ahead gates the start of P0 implementation.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:53:## 1. METADATA
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:58:| **Priority** | P0 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:59:| **Status** | Ruling settled — adopt the phased path (P0→P4), decided on the analysis; reversible and operator-overridable. No runtime implementation started; a separate operator go-ahead gates P0. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:61:| **Branch** | `skilled/v4.0.0.0` |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:62:| **Migration stage** | Decision gate preceding P0 (documentation + observability); default-on is the P4 outcome |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:63:| **Blast radius** | Decision + contracts only (no code change here). The contracts it governs range from zero-blast (docs) to the highest-blast change in the program (global serving default), each staged and reversible |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:69:## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:71:### Problem Statement
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:73:The parent goal frames "compiled routing as the effective default" as a switch to flip. Verified source evidence shows that framing is unsafe for five independent, non-overlapping reasons:
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:75:1. **Zero routing benefit today.** The only place compiled routing enters the live advisor is `enrichCompiledRoutes()` (`advisor-recommend.ts:357`). With the flag unset it is a pure pass-through (`:362`). With the flag on, it maps over recommendations the legacy path already produced and, per recommendation, attaches `compiledRoute` as an additive sibling field — `{ ...recommendation, compiledRoute }` (`:371`) — never recomputing `skillId`/`workflowMode`. Enabling the flag cannot change which skill is chosen.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:76:2. **Silent drift is the steady state.** The serve-time shim recomputes the decision from live hub config; on any mismatch, missing resolver, or error it emits a `{ servingAuthority: "legacy" }` sentinel (`compiled-route.cjs:36-39`), which the advisor maps to `undefined` (`advisor-recommend.ts:351`). Any edit to a hub's `SKILL.md`/router config reverts that hub to legacy invisibly until its manifest is re-minted. This repo churns hub config constantly, so "compiled" would spend much of its life silently on legacy.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:77:3. **No observability.** Nothing distinguishes "serving compiled" from "silently fell back to legacy." A drifted hub and a broken hub read identically.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:78:4. **Undocumented flag = governance violation.** `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is absent from `ENV-REFERENCE.md`, which the project constitution (CLAUDE.md §6) mandates as the source of truth for flag defaults. Flipping an undocumented flag violates that mandate.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:79:5. **Kill-switch inversion.** Today, absence-of-var = legacy = safe. After a naive default-flip, absence = compiled, silently changing every runtime/hook/CI/launcher that assumed "absent = legacy."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:81:A sixth, structural fragility (found this phase, under-weighted in prior handovers): the runtime front door `bin/compiled-route.cjs` resolves its resolver from a path **inside the spec tree** (`compiled-route.cjs:16-21` → `007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs`). A spec renumber/re-nest silently breaks every compiled route to the legacy sentinel — the repo's own reorganization is a drift engine.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:83:### Purpose
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:85:Record the decision that default-on is a Phase-4 *outcome*, not a switch, and specify the four contracts (P0→P4) that make an eventual global default-on safe, observable, and byte-exact reversible — so that when the flag is flipped, compiled routing does something legacy cannot, drift is caught by CI rather than discovered in production, and the kill-switch (`=0`) is a documented, load-bearing control rather than an accident of variable absence.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:92:## 3. SCOPE
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:94:### In Scope
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:96:- The **ruling** (settled): default-on is a staged P4 outcome; the phased path P0→P4 is adopted as the program of record, decided on the analysis and reversible. A separate operator go-ahead gates the start of P0 implementation.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:97:- The **fallback contract**: a precise, single-sourced definition of "graceful backwards-compat for skills lacking the compiled JSONs/snapshot" — no-manifest OR stale-hash resolves to the legacy sentinel; the `sk-git` non-hub template stays pinned legacy.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:98:- The **drift-detection CI contract**: recompute each hub's live config hash vs its minted manifest; fail "re-mint required" on mismatch; wire "edit a hub → re-mint" as an enforced rule, not a remembered one.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:99:- The **observability contract**: the verify harness must classify drift-to-legacy as *degraded/expected*, not *broken*, and expose a per-hub serving-status readout (compiled-serving | legacy-fallback | drifted).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:100:- The **migration map** P0→P4 with reversibility and the frozen-scorer pin at every step, including promoting or explicitly documenting the runtime→spec-tree resolver coupling as a named drift source.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:102:### Out of Scope
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:105:- Editing the frozen benchmark scorer (`router-replay.cjs`, `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`, `load-playbook-scenarios.cjs`) — [why] pinned and non-negotiable across the whole program.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:106:- Actually flipping `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` to a repo default in this phase — [why] this phase decides and contracts; the flip is the P4 execution phase, gated on P0–P3 landing green.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:107:- The `sk-doc:create-skill` generator alignment and the skill-benchmark alignment — [why] delivered in the sibling phases `013-create-skill-alignment` and `014-benchmark-alignment`, which consume this phase's fallback and eligibility contracts.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:109:### Files to Change
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:113:| `012-default-on-decision/spec.md` | Create | This decision spec |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:114:| `012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md` | Create | The ruling, the verified evidence with file:line receipts, alternatives weighed, and the fallback/drift/observability contracts in full |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:115:| `012-default-on-decision/{plan.md, tasks.md, checklist.md, implementation-summary.md}` | Create | Level-3 planning, task breakdown, verification checklist, and Planned-state completion record |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:117:> This phase authors documentation and contracts only. No runtime file, `SKILL.md`, manifest, or scorer is edited here.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:124:## 4. REQUIREMENTS
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:126:### P0 - Blockers (MUST complete)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:130:| REQ-001 | State the ruling and its evidence such that each of the five premise-failures and the sixth structural fragility is backed by a verifiable file:line receipt, distinguishing confirmed from inferred. | `decision-record.md` lists each finding with its receipt (e.g. additive metadata `advisor-recommend.ts:371`; sentinel `compiled-route.cjs:36-39`; flag absent from `ENV-REFERENCE.md`; allowlist duplicated in `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` + `HUB_CHILD`; resolver spec-path coupling `compiled-route.cjs:16-21`); no load-bearing claim is unsourced. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:131:| REQ-002 | Specify the fallback contract precisely and single-sourced. | The contract defines that a hub is compiled-served IFF a valid, fresh manifest exists AND `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=1` AND the hub is eligible; every other state resolves to the legacy sentinel with no behavior change. The eligibility predicate is named as the single source both `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` and `HUB_CHILD` must derive from (delivered in P3). |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:132:| REQ-003 | Specify the drift-detection CI contract. | The contract defines: recompute each hub's live config hash, compare to its minted manifest digest, exit non-zero with "re-mint required: <hub>" on mismatch; and the enforced rule "editing a hub's routing inputs requires re-minting its manifest in the same change." |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:133:| REQ-004 | Specify the observability contract. | The contract defines a per-hub serving-status readout with three states (compiled-serving | legacy-fallback | drifted) and requires the verify harness to score drift-to-legacy as degraded/expected rather than a hard failure, so a red signal means breakage, not routine churn. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:134:| REQ-005 | Record the P0→P4 migration map with reversibility and the frozen-scorer pin at every step, and name the runtime→spec-tree resolver coupling as a P0 remediation (promote the resolver to a stable runtime path OR document the coupling as an explicit drift source). | `decision-record.md` and `plan.md` carry the ordered P0→P4 map; each step names its rollback; the scorer pin and "no routing-decision change" invariant are restated per step. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:136:### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:141:| REQ-007 | Cross-link the two dependent alignment phases so the fallback and eligibility contracts have exactly one home. | `013-create-skill-alignment` and `014-benchmark-alignment` reference this phase's contracts rather than restating them; this spec's RELATED DOCUMENTS lists both. |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:148:## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:150:- **SC-001**: The decision is legible — a reader can reconstruct, from receipts, why flipping the default today is zero-benefit and why the phased path is recommended, without re-deriving it from source.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:151:- **SC-002**: The fallback contract is unambiguous and single-sourced: "no valid fresh manifest ⇒ legacy" holds by construction, and the eligibility predicate has one named home for P3 to implement.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:152:- **SC-003**: The drift-CI and observability contracts are specified concretely enough to implement in P0/P1 without further design.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:153:- **SC-004**: The P0→P4 map is reversible at every step, restates the frozen-scorer pin and the no-routing-change invariant per step, and names the resolver spec-path coupling as a P0 remediation.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:154:- **SC-005**: The ruling's status honestly reflects reality — settled on the analysis (adopt the phased path), reversible and operator-overridable — with no premature "default-on" or "implementation started" claim.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:161:## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:165:| Risk | Premise capture — treating default-on as a switch | Flips an undocumented flag that inverts the kill-switch for zero routing benefit | This decision reframes default-on as a P4 outcome gated on P0–P3; the flip is never this phase's action |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:166:| Risk | Silent drift normalized as "compiled" | A drifted hub serves legacy while dashboards claim compiled | P1 drift-CI fails re-mint-required; P0 observability distinguishes drifted from broken |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:167:| Risk | Duplicated allowlist diverges | `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` and `HUB_CHILD` drift apart, mis-gating hubs | P3 single-sources eligibility to "valid fresh manifest exists"; both predicates derive from it |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:168:| Risk | Runtime resolver coupled to a spec-tree path | A spec renumber breaks all compiled routing to the sentinel | REQ-005 P0 remediation: promote the resolver to a stable runtime path or document the coupling as a named drift source with a guard |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:170:| Dependency | Sibling `013`/`014` alignment phases | Onboarding (create-skill) and validation (benchmarks) must consume this phase's contracts | REQ-007 cross-links; the contracts live here once and are referenced, not restated |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:177:## 7. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:179:### Reversibility
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:180:- **NFR-R01**: Every step P0→P4 names an explicit rollback; the P4 global default-on keeps `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the documented, load-bearing kill-switch.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:183:### Determinism
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:184:- **NFR-D01**: The fallback is deterministic: identical (hub config, manifest, flag) inputs always yield the same served-authority; drift is a pure function of a hash mismatch, not timing.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:186:### Authority
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:187:- **NFR-A01**: Serving authority is conferred only by a valid, fresh manifest under an enabled flag for an eligible hub; nothing else grants it, and the eligibility predicate has exactly one source of truth (P3).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:191:## 8. EDGE CASES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:193:### Fallback correctness
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:194:- Hub with no manifest (a freshly created skill, pre-`013`): resolves to the legacy sentinel; routing unchanged — backward-compat by construction.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:195:- Hub with a stale manifest (config edited, not re-minted): live hash ≠ minted digest ⇒ legacy sentinel; P1 CI fails re-mint-required.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:197:### Observability boundaries
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:198:- Drifted hub vs broken resolver: both currently read identically; P0 observability must separate "degraded/expected (drift)" from "broken (error)".
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:201:### Kill-switch
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:202:- `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` after P4 default-on: must fully restore legacy serving fleet-wide, documented as the kill-switch, not an incidental default.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:206:## 9. COMPLEXITY ASSESSMENT
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:211:| Risk | 18/25 | The decision governs the highest-blast change in the program (the global serving default); the phase itself is zero-blast documentation, but its ruling is load-bearing for every later phase |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:212:| Research | 12/20 | Mechanism verified from source this phase (additive metadata, sentinel fallback, allowlist duplication, resolver coupling); residual is P0 implementation, not investigation |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:217:## 10. RISK MATRIX
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:221:| Operator overrides to flip default-on now | Medium | Medium | Fallback is genuinely fail-safe today, so an early flip is survivable; still land P0 docs + observability first to satisfy governance and avoid a two-meaning red signal | Operator |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:222:| A hub edit silently reverts that hub to legacy | High | Medium | P1 drift-CI fails re-mint-required at edit time; P0 readout shows the drifted state | P1 owner |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:223:| The two hardcoded allowlists diverge | Medium | High | P3 single-sources eligibility to "valid fresh manifest exists"; both predicates derive from it | P3 owner |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:224:| A spec renumber severs the runtime resolver path | Medium | High | ADR-003: promote the resolver to a stable runtime path (recommended) or guard the path loudly | P0 owner |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:225:| Frozen scorer edited, invalidating the parity baseline | Low | High | Hard pin restated per migration step; never edited; re-hash gate aborts on drift | Whole program |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:229:## 11. USER STORIES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:231:- **US-001 (operator).** As the operator overseeing the cutover, I want the default-on question recorded with verifiable receipts and the settled ruling, so I can see how it was decided and override to flip-now if I choose, with full information rather than a narrative.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:232:- **US-002 (skill author).** As someone creating a new hub via `create-skill`, I want compiled eligibility to follow from minting a manifest, so my skill onboards by a documented step and, until then, routes via legacy by construction instead of being silently half-wired.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:234:- **US-004 (release owner).** As the owner of the eventual global flip, I want a per-hub serving-status readout and a documented `=0` kill-switch, so I can flip hub-by-hub, watch each land, and revert instantly if any hub misbehaves.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:238:## 12. OPEN QUESTIONS
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:240:- **Q1 (resolved).** The ruling is settled: adopt the phased path (default-on as a staged P4 outcome after P0–P3), decided on the analysis and reversible. An operator override to flip `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` on now remains available but is not blocking; the steelman for flipping now is recorded in `decision-record.md` ("flip it when compiled does something legacy can't").
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:241:- **Q2.** For the P0 resolver-coupling remediation: promote `resolve.cjs` out of the spec tree into a stable runtime location, or keep it in place behind a path-integrity guard that fails loudly on a renumber? (Recommendation: promote; it removes the drift source rather than guarding it.)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:242:- **Q3.** Which single env profile hosts the P2 canary default-on (repo default staying off), and what parity + clean-fallback thresholds gate promotion from P2 to P3?
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:248:## RELATED DOCUMENTS
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:251:- **Build approach (P0→P4)**: See `plan.md`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:256:- **Live integration point**: `system-skill-advisor/mcp-server/handlers/advisor-recommend.ts` (`enrichCompiledRoutes`, `compiledRouteForRecommendation`)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/spec.md:257:- **Onboarding alignment (consumes fallback/eligibility contracts)**: `../013-create-skill-alignment/`
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:3:description: "Three decisions governing whether and how SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING becomes the repo's effective default: defer global default-on to a staged P4 outcome, single-source compiled eligibility to a valid fresh manifest, and remediate the runtime-to-spec-tree resolver coupling."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:5:  - "compiled routing default-on decision record"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:12:    packet_pointer: "sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:16:    next_safe_action: "Begin P0 on operator go-ahead"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:28:      - "Flip the default now or adopt the phased path? Adopt the phased path (ADR-001), settled on the analysis; operator may override."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:31:# Decision Record: Compiled Routing Default-On
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:35:<!-- HVR_REFERENCE: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/hvr-rules.md -->
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:40:## ADR-001: Defer global default-on to a staged P4 outcome
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:42:### Metadata
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:53:### Context
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:55:The parent goal asks to make compiled routing the effective default, framing it as flipping `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` from off to on. Reading the live integration point shows that framing buys nothing and costs real surface. The advisor enters compiled routing only through `enrichCompiledRoutes()` at `advisor-recommend.ts:357`. With the flag unset that function returns its input untouched (`:362`). With the flag set it maps over recommendations the legacy path already computed and attaches `compiledRoute` as an additive sibling field, `{ ...recommendation, compiledRoute }` at `:371`, and never recomputes the chosen `skillId` or `workflowMode`. Turning the flag on can only make that extra field appear or, on drift, silently not appear. It cannot change which skill is recommended.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:57:The sibling `011-runtime-engine` already flipped all seven hubs' manifests to `servingAuthority: compiled`, held inert behind the default-off flag. So the destination machinery exists. What does not exist is the reason to flip: today the flip is behavior-neutral by construction.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:59:### Constraints
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:62:- The three frozen benchmark scorer files (`router-replay.cjs`, `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`, `load-playbook-scenarios.cjs`) are pinned and never edited.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:63:- `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` is absent from `ENV-REFERENCE.md`, which CLAUDE.md section 6 mandates as the source of truth for flag defaults. Flipping an undocumented flag violates that mandate.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:64:- The serve-time shim recomputes each hub's decision from live config and falls back to a `{ servingAuthority: "legacy" }` sentinel on any mismatch (`compiled-route.cjs:36-39`), which the advisor maps to `undefined` (`advisor-recommend.ts:351`). Editing a hub reverts it to legacy until re-minted, with nothing to observe the reversion.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:71:### Decision
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:73:**We chose**: Treat global default-on as the final outcome of a four-step program (P0 through P4), not a one-line default change made now.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:75:**How it works**: P0 documents the flag in `ENV-REFERENCE.md` and makes the verify harness distinguish drift-to-legacy from breakage plus a per-hub serving-status readout. P1 adds a drift-detection CI that recomputes each hub's live hash against its minted manifest and fails re-mint-required. P2 canaries default-on in one env profile while the repo default stays off. P3 replaces the two hardcoded allowlists with a data-driven eligibility rule (see ADR-002). P4 flips the repo default hub-by-hub, keeping `=0` as the documented kill-switch. The flip becomes worthwhile precisely when compiled routing does something legacy cannot (a consumed decision, a caught drift), which P0 through P3 create.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:77:**Settlement**: This ruling is settled on the merits of the analysis above (the five premise-failures and the resolver coupling), as the session directive to settle the decision using the fresh-Opus analysis requires. It is a reversible documentation decision: no runtime change follows from it, and the operator may override to flip-now at any time. Acceptance settles the sequencing (phased) only; a separate operator go-ahead gates the start of P0 implementation.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:84:### Alternatives Considered
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:88:| **Phased P0 to P4 (chosen)** | Reversible at every step; drift caught by CI not production; flag documented before it is load-bearing; the flip lands when it carries benefit | Four phases of enabling work before the headline default flips | 9/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:89:| Flip the repo default now | One-line change; matches the literal goal wording | Zero routing benefit (additive metadata only); normalizes silent drift; inverts the kill-switch (absence becomes compiled); violates the ENV-REFERENCE governance mandate | 3/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:90:| Abandon compiled routing | Removes the drift surface entirely | Discards a built, proven, reversible system and the parity work behind it; loses the future benefit the phased path unlocks | 2/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:92:**Why this one**: The destination (compiled as the effective default) is not rejected, it is sequenced. Flipping today trades governance and observability surface for a benefit that is currently zero, so the correct move is to build the benefit and the safety net first, then flip. The steelman for flipping now is honest and recorded: if compiled cannot help and cannot hurt routing, the only net effects are the ones that can hurt, so flip it once compiled does something legacy cannot. That condition is exactly what P0 through P3 establish.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:99:### Consequences
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:102:- The eventual flip is observable: a per-hub readout shows compiled-serving vs legacy-fallback vs drifted, so a red signal means breakage rather than routine churn.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:104:- The kill-switch stays meaningful: `=0` remains the documented control, and variable-absence keeps its safe legacy meaning until the P4 flip deliberately changes it.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:107:- Four phases of enabling work precede the headline default change. Mitigation: each phase ships standalone value (docs, CI, canary, single-sourced eligibility) rather than being pure overhead.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:113:| Operator overrides to flip now | M | The fallback is genuinely fail-safe today, so an early flip is survivable; but P0 documentation and observability should still land first to satisfy governance and avoid a two-meaning red signal |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:121:### Five Checks Evaluation
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:125:| 1 | **Necessary?** | PASS | The governance gap (undocumented flag) and the silent-drift surface are real today, independent of any future flip |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:129:| 5 | **Open Horizons?** | PASS | Data-driven eligibility (ADR-002) scales to every future skill, so the path does not paint the fleet into a hardcoded corner |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:138:### Implementation
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:141:- P0: `ENV-REFERENCE.md` gains the flag entry; the verify harness gains drift-vs-breakage classification and a per-hub serving-status readout.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:142:- P1: a drift-detection CI job plus the enforced rule that editing a hub's routing inputs re-mints its manifest in the same change.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:143:- P2 to P4: a canary env profile, the data-driven eligibility rule (ADR-002), then the staged hub-by-hub default flip.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:145:**How to roll back**: Nothing in this phase changes runtime behavior, so there is nothing to roll back here. Across the program, `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` restores legacy serving fleet-wide, and each per-hub flip retains a byte-identical prior manifest for a byte-exact per-hub revert.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:153:## ADR-002: Single-source compiled eligibility to a valid fresh manifest
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:155:### Metadata
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:159:| **Status** | Accepted (design direction; implemented in P3) |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:166:### Context
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:168:Which hubs are compiled-eligible is hardcoded in two places: `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` in `advisor-recommend.ts:41` and `HUB_CHILD` in `compiled-route.cjs:23`. Two hand-maintained lists drift apart. A newly created skill is compiled-invisible with no defined way to opt in, and `create-skill` today has zero compiled-routing awareness (a repo grep for compiled-routing tokens under the create-skill mode returns nothing).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:170:### Constraints
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:172:- Backward-compat is required: a skill lacking the compiled JSONs or snapshot must route via legacy with no behavior change.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:180:### Decision
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:182:**We chose**: Define compiled eligibility as a single derived predicate: a hub is compiled-eligible if and only if a valid, fresh manifest exists for it (its minted digest matches its live config hash). Both `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` and `HUB_CHILD` derive from that one rule.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:184:**How it works**: Onboarding a skill means minting its manifest; backward-compat means the absence of a manifest yields legacy by construction. `create-skill` (phase 013) mints or scaffolds the manifest step so new hubs are born either compiled-ready or explicitly legacy, never silently half-wired.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:191:### Alternatives Considered
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:196:| One hardcoded list imported by both | Removes duplication cheaply | Still manual; a new skill still needs a code edit to onboard | 6/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:206:### Consequences
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:209:- The two allowlists cannot diverge because neither is authored by hand.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:210:- A new or edited skill has one clear compiled state derived from whether its manifest is fresh.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:220:| Migration removes the hardcoded sets prematurely | M | Keep the sets as a pinned fallback until P3 parity is proven, then delete in one change |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:227:### Five Checks Evaluation
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:231:| 1 | **Necessary?** | PASS | Two hardcoded allowlists exist now and will diverge; new skills have no onboarding path |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:233:| 3 | **Sufficient?** | PASS | One derived predicate covers eligibility, onboarding, and backward-compat together |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:234:| 4 | **Fits Goal?** | PASS | Directly enables a safe global default-on by making eligibility a maintained property, not a code constant |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:235:| 5 | **Open Horizons?** | PASS | Scales to any number of future skills with no code edit per skill |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:244:### Implementation
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:247:- P3: a single eligibility predicate keyed on manifest freshness; `COMPILED_ROUTING_HUBS` and `HUB_CHILD` become derived, then removed as hand-authored constants.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:248:- Phase 013: `create-skill` scaffolds the manifest step so onboarding mints eligibility.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:250:**How to roll back**: Retain the hardcoded sets as a pinned fallback through P3; if the derived predicate misbehaves, restore the constants (a one-file revert in each of the two locations).
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:258:## ADR-003: Remediate the runtime-to-spec-tree resolver coupling
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:260:### Metadata
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:264:| **Status** | Accepted (P0 remediation; promote the resolver) |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:271:### Context
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:273:The runtime front door `.opencode/bin/compiled-route.cjs` resolves its resolver from a path inside the spec tree: `compiled-route.cjs:16-21` points at `007-unified-refactor-implementation/011-runtime-engine/lib/resolve.cjs`. This repo renumbers and re-nests spec folders constantly (the memory index records repeated hyphen migrations, renumbers, and re-nests). A single such move silently breaks every compiled route to the legacy sentinel, with no observable signal. The repo's own reorganization is a latent drift engine independent of hub-config edits.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:275:### Constraints
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:285:### Decision
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:296:### Alternatives Considered
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:300:| **Promote resolver to a runtime path (chosen)** | Removes the drift source rather than guarding it; runtime no longer depends on spec-tree layout | A small build or copy step to keep the runtime copy current | 8/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:302:| Leave as-is and document | No work now | The drift source remains and stays silent; documentation does not stop a renumber | 4/10 |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:311:### Consequences
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:324:| Runtime copy goes stale vs authored source | M | Add a freshness check to the drift-CI (P1) so a stale runtime resolver fails the same gate as a stale manifest |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:331:### Five Checks Evaluation
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:338:| 4 | **Fits Goal?** | PASS | A default-on fleet cannot rest on a resolver that a spec move can sever |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:348:### Implementation
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:351:- P0: move `resolve.cjs` to a runtime path; update the shim's require; keep the authored source building or copying into place.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:352:- P1: the drift-CI also checks the runtime resolver is current with its authored source.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/decision-record.md:364:HVR rules: .opencode/skills/sk-doc/references/hvr-rules.md
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:3:description: "Planned P0-to-P4 delivery sequence for the default-on ruling: establish flag governance and serving observability, enforce drift detection, run a bounded canary, single-source eligibility, then stage the global default-on cutover with a documented kill-switch."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:5:  - "compiled routing default-on implementation plan"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:6:  - "P0 P4 compiled routing migration"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:12:    packet_pointer: "sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:15:    recent_action: "Prepared the Planned P0-to-P4 supporting plan"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:16:    next_safe_action: "Begin P0 on operator go-ahead"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:31:      - "Which environment profile will host the P2 canary?"
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:33:      - "Flip the default now or adopt the phased path? Adopt the phased path, settled on the analysis; operator may override."
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:35:# Implementation Plan: Compiled Routing Default-On Safe Cutover
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:50:## 1. SUMMARY
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:52:### Technical Context
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:57:| **Current authority** | Compiled manifests are present for seven hubs, but the runtime flag is off by default |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:59:| **Protected baseline** | `router-replay.cjs`, `score-skill-benchmark.cjs`, and `load-playbook-scenarios.cjs` remain frozen |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:60:| **Verification** | Per-hub serving status, route-gold parity, drift CI, canary evidence, and kill-switch drills |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:62:### Overview
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:64:The recommended approach is the ordered P0-to-P4 program already ruled in `decision-record.md`. P0 makes the current flag and fallback state legible, separates drift from breakage in the harness, exposes serving status per hub, and removes or explicitly guards the resolver's dependency on a spec-tree path. P1 through P4 then add drift CI, a one-profile canary, data-driven eligibility, and a hub-by-hub global default change.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:72:## 2. QUALITY GATES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:74:### Definition of Ready
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:77:- [ ] The fallback, drift-CI, observability, and migration contracts in `spec.md` and `decision-record.md` are treated as authoritative.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:79:- [ ] The P2 canary environment profile and promotion owner are named.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:81:### Definition of Done
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:83:- [ ] P0 through P4 acceptance evidence is recorded without changing routing decisions.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:84:- [ ] The flag is documented before any default changes.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:85:- [ ] Drift is surfaced as drift, resolver breakage is surfaced as breakage, and per-hub authority is inspectable.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:86:- [ ] The two eligibility consumers derive from one manifest-freshness predicate.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:87:- [ ] `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` is exercised as the fleet-wide kill-switch after the staged cutover.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:94:## 3. ARCHITECTURE
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:96:### Pattern
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:98:Observe, enforce, canary, derive, then cut over. Serving authority remains data-driven and fail-safe: runtime consumption is gated by the environment flag and per-hub eligibility, while a missing or stale manifest follows the legacy path defined by the authoritative contract.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:100:### Key Components
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:102:- **Environment contract**: documents the flag's current default, explicit enablement, and `=0` kill-switch.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:103:- **Serving-status probe**: reports `compiled-serving`, `legacy-fallback`, or `drifted` for each hub and separates expected degradation from execution failure.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:105:- **Eligibility resolver**: supplies the single derived predicate consumed by both current allowlist sites.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:106:- **Canary profile**: enables the compiled path in one bounded environment while the repository default remains off.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:107:- **Staged cutover controller**: changes the two runtime predicates and the seven hub directives in lockstep, one hub at a time.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:109:### Data Flow
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:128:## FIX ADDENDUM: AFFECTED SURFACES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:132:| `ENV-REFERENCE.md` | Source of truth for environment defaults | Document the flag, current default, explicit enablement, and `=0` kill-switch | Documentation lint plus runtime default/override probes |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:133:| Verify harness | Treats fallback outcomes without enough cause detail | Add drift-vs-breakage classification and a per-hub status readout | Fresh, stale, missing, and broken fixtures |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:136:| Environment profiles | Repository default remains off | Enable one named canary profile only | Profile-specific flag assertion; all other profiles remain off |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:137:| Eligibility consumers | Two hand-maintained hub sets | Derive both from the single manifest-freshness predicate | Consumer parity and no-manifest legacy case |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:138:| Hub directives and runtime defaults | Seven additive directives, default-off predicate | Stage P4 changes in lockstep, one hub at a time | Per-hub route parity, status readout, and `=0` rollback |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:143:- Locate every read of `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` and every environment profile that can set it.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:152:## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:154:### Phase 1: Setup (P0 governance and observability)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:156:- [ ] Document `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` in the environment reference with default-off semantics and the explicit `=0` kill-switch.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:157:- [ ] Extend the verify harness so drift-to-legacy is reported as degraded/expected while a broken resolver remains a hard failure.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:159:- [ ] Remediate the runtime-to-spec-tree resolver coupling by promoting the resolver to a stable runtime path; if the operator rejects promotion, add a loud path-integrity guard and document the residual drift source.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:160:- [ ] Re-hash the three frozen scorer files before and after P0.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:163:### Phase 2: Implementation (P1 and P2 enforcement)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:165:- [ ] P1: add CI that recomputes each hub's live routing-input hash and compares it with the minted manifest digest.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:166:- [ ] P1: fail with `re-mint required: <hub>` whenever a routing input changes without a matching manifest update.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:167:- [ ] P2: select one environment profile and enable compiled routing only there; keep the repository default and all other profiles off.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:168:- [ ] P2: record parity, serving-status, drift, and fallback evidence for the canary.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:169:- [ ] Re-hash the frozen scorer files after P1 and P2.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:170:- [ ] Rollback: disable the drift-CI job without removing its diagnostic command; unset the canary override or set it to `0`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:172:### Phase 3: Verification and Cutover (P3 and P4)
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:174:- [ ] P3: implement one data-driven eligibility predicate using the valid-fresh-manifest rule from `decision-record.md`.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:175:- [ ] P3: make both existing eligibility consumers derive from that predicate, retaining the old constants as a temporary rollback path until parity is proven.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:176:- [ ] P4: change the repository default in a staged hub order, updating the two runtime predicates and each hub directive in lockstep.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:177:- [ ] P4: after every hub, require route-gold parity, a `compiled-serving` status, clean fallback behavior, and unchanged scorer hashes before proceeding.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:178:- [ ] P4: exercise `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the fleet-wide kill-switch and retain per-hub manifest rollback.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:185:## 5. TESTING STRATEGY
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:189:| Documentation | Environment flag entry and kill-switch semantics | Reference lint and targeted text assertions |
