.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:194:| Canary | One environment profile only | Profile matrix proving the repository default remains off |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:195:| Rollback | Per-hub authority and fleet kill-switch | Prior-manifest restore plus `=0` legacy-serving proof |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:202:## 6. DEPENDENCIES
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:208:| Create-skill onboarding alignment | Sibling phase | Planned | Future hubs cannot self-onboard as compiled-ready |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:210:| Stable resolver location decision | Architecture | Pending | P0 must either remove or explicitly guard the spec-tree coupling |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:211:| Named P2 canary profile | Operations | Pending | Canary enablement cannot be bounded or audited |
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:218:## 7. ROLLBACK PLAN
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:221:- **Procedure**: Stop the stage; set `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` for fleet-wide legacy serving; restore the affected hub's retained prior manifest when a per-hub pointer changed; restore the prior resolver location or temporary eligibility constants when those components caused the failure; rerun the status and parity gates before resuming.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:222:- **Preserved gains**: Earlier documentation, read-only diagnostics, and drift evidence remain unless they caused the fault. Rollback targets the smallest stage that introduced the regression.
.opencode/specs/sk-doc/019-sk-doc-router-alignment/020-router-unification-program/007-unified-refactor-implementation/012-default-on-decision/plan.md:228:## L2: PHASE DEPENDENCIES
