   378	<!-- ANCHOR:ai-execution -->
   379	## L3: AI EXECUTION PROTOCOL
   380	
   381	### Pre-Task Checklist
   382	
   383	- Confirm the operator go-ahead to begin is recorded before starting P0.
   384	- Read every target file and the authoritative decision contracts before editing.
   385	- Capture the frozen-scorer digests and the relevant baseline gate before each stage.
   386	- Confirm the change list remains inside the authorized stage and names a byte-exact or flag-based rollback.
   387	
   388	### Execution Rules
   389	
   390	| Rule | Requirement |
   391	|------|-------------|
   392	| Ordered gates | Do not start a later stage until all earlier stage exit criteria are evidenced |
   393	| Scope lock | Modify only surfaces named by the authorized stage; route unrelated work to Follow-ups |
   394	| Frozen scorer | Treat the three pinned scorer files as read-only and fail on digest drift |
   395	| Reversibility | Preserve `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` and each stage's rollback evidence |
   396	| Evidence | Keep tasks and checklist items unchecked until the named command or artifact exists |
   397	
   398	### Status Reporting Format
   399	
   400	```text
   401	Stage: [P0|P1|P2|P3|P4]
   402	Status: [planned|in-progress|blocked|verified]
   403	Changed surfaces: [paths]
   404	Parity and scorer pin: [command + result]
   405	Rollback evidence: [command or artifact]
   406	Next safe action: [single stage-local action]
   407	```
   408	
   409	### Blocked Task Protocol
   410	
   411	If parity fails, a frozen digest changes, serving status is ambiguous, or rollback cannot be proved, stop the current stage. Preserve the failing evidence and report the exact command, exit code, affected hub or profile, and last verified rollback point before proposing a narrower remediation.
   412	<!-- /ANCHOR:ai-execution -->
