    95	
    96	### Pattern
    97	
    98	Observe, enforce, canary, derive, then cut over. Serving authority remains data-driven and fail-safe: runtime consumption is gated by the environment flag and per-hub eligibility, while a missing or stale manifest follows the legacy path defined by the authoritative contract.
    99	
   100	### Key Components
   101	
   102	- **Environment contract**: documents the flag's current default, explicit enablement, and `=0` kill-switch.
   103	- **Serving-status probe**: reports `compiled-serving`, `legacy-fallback`, or `drifted` for each hub and separates expected degradation from execution failure.
   104	- **Drift CI**: recomputes live routing-input hashes and rejects stale manifests with a re-mint-required message.
   105	- **Eligibility resolver**: supplies the single derived predicate consumed by both current allowlist sites.
   106	- **Canary profile**: enables the compiled path in one bounded environment while the repository default remains off.
   107	- **Staged cutover controller**: changes the two runtime predicates and the seven hub directives in lockstep, one hub at a time.
   108	
   109	### Data Flow
   110	
   111	```text
   112	hub routing inputs
   113	      |
   114	      v
   115	freshness check ---- stale/missing ----> legacy path + explicit status
   116	      |
   117	      v fresh
   118	flag + serving gate ---- disabled -----> legacy path + explicit status
   119	      |
   120	      v enabled
   121	compiled decision ---- parity gate ----> served only when legacy-equivalent
   122	```
   123	<!-- /ANCHOR:architecture -->
   124	
   125	---
   126	
   127	<!-- ANCHOR:affected-surfaces -->
   128	## FIX ADDENDUM: AFFECTED SURFACES
   129	
   130	| Surface | Current Role | Planned Action | Verification |
   131	|---------|--------------|----------------|--------------|
   132	| `ENV-REFERENCE.md` | Source of truth for environment defaults | Document the flag, current default, explicit enablement, and `=0` kill-switch | Documentation lint plus runtime default/override probes |
   133	| Verify harness | Treats fallback outcomes without enough cause detail | Add drift-vs-breakage classification and a per-hub status readout | Fresh, stale, missing, and broken fixtures |
   134	| Runtime resolver/front door | Reads a resolver beneath the spec tree | Promote the resolver to a stable runtime path, or guard and document the coupling if promotion is rejected | Spec-tree move simulation and fail-safe fallback check |
   135	| CI | Does not enforce manifest freshness | Add live-hash versus minted-digest comparison | Positive fresh case and negative re-mint-required case |
   136	| Environment profiles | Repository default remains off | Enable one named canary profile only | Profile-specific flag assertion; all other profiles remain off |
   137	| Eligibility consumers | Two hand-maintained hub sets | Derive both from the single manifest-freshness predicate | Consumer parity and no-manifest legacy case |
   138	| Hub directives and runtime defaults | Seven additive directives, default-off predicate | Stage P4 changes in lockstep, one hub at a time | Per-hub route parity, status readout, and `=0` rollback |
   139	| Frozen scorer files | Stable route-gold baseline | Read and hash only; never edit | Before/after digest equality per stage |
   140	
   141	Required inventories before implementation:
   142	
   143	- Locate every read of `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` and every environment profile that can set it.
   144	- Locate both current eligibility sets and every caller that assumes their shape.
   145	- Record all seven hub directives and their exact fallback behavior.
   146	- Record the resolver's current spec-tree dependency before choosing promotion or an explicit guard.
   147	<!-- /ANCHOR:affected-surfaces -->
   148	
   149	---
   150	
   151	<!-- ANCHOR:phases -->
   152	## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES
   153	
   154	### Phase 1: Setup (P0 governance and observability)
   155	
   156	- [ ] Document `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` in the environment reference with default-off semantics and the explicit `=0` kill-switch.
   157	- [ ] Extend the verify harness so drift-to-legacy is reported as degraded/expected while a broken resolver remains a hard failure.
   158	- [ ] Add the per-hub serving-status readout required by the observability contract.
   159	- [ ] Remediate the runtime-to-spec-tree resolver coupling by promoting the resolver to a stable runtime path; if the operator rejects promotion, add a loud path-integrity guard and document the residual drift source.
   160	- [ ] Re-hash the three frozen scorer files before and after P0.
   161	- [ ] Rollback: revert the documentation, harness, and resolver-location changes; keep the flag off and restore the prior resolver path if promotion was attempted.
   162	
   163	### Phase 2: Implementation (P1 and P2 enforcement)
   164	
   165	- [ ] P1: add CI that recomputes each hub's live routing-input hash and compares it with the minted manifest digest.
   166	- [ ] P1: fail with `re-mint required: <hub>` whenever a routing input changes without a matching manifest update.
   167	- [ ] P2: select one environment profile and enable compiled routing only there; keep the repository default and all other profiles off.
   168	- [ ] P2: record parity, serving-status, drift, and fallback evidence for the canary.
   169	- [ ] Re-hash the frozen scorer files after P1 and P2.
   170	- [ ] Rollback: disable the drift-CI job without removing its diagnostic command; unset the canary override or set it to `0`.
   171	
   172	### Phase 3: Verification and Cutover (P3 and P4)
   173	
   174	- [ ] P3: implement one data-driven eligibility predicate using the valid-fresh-manifest rule from `decision-record.md`.
   175	- [ ] P3: make both existing eligibility consumers derive from that predicate, retaining the old constants as a temporary rollback path until parity is proven.
   176	- [ ] P4: change the repository default in a staged hub order, updating the two runtime predicates and each hub directive in lockstep.
   177	- [ ] P4: after every hub, require route-gold parity, a `compiled-serving` status, clean fallback behavior, and unchanged scorer hashes before proceeding.
   178	- [ ] P4: exercise `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING=0` as the fleet-wide kill-switch and retain per-hub manifest rollback.
   179	- [ ] Rollback: stop at the first failed gate, set the flag to `0`, restore the affected hub's prior authority, and, if needed, restore the temporary hardcoded eligibility constants.
   180	<!-- /ANCHOR:phases -->
