codex
Two concrete execution blockers have emerged beyond the packet’s current wording. First, the advisor launcher strips `SPECKIT_COMPILED_ROUTING` before spawning the daemon, so a canary profile set in the parent environment cannot activate the live advisor path. Second, both “default” predicates are fleet-global; changing either once affects every already-compiled manifest, so the proposed hub-by-hub P4 cannot be implemented literally without a separate per-hub cohort gate.
exec
